The paper deals with optimization problems related to pricing and demand in economics, which are often studied in the field of computational game theory (cs.GT). The use of gradient-based algorithms suggests a focus on optimization and algorithms (cs.DS), while the study of valuation functions and production cost functions suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with social welfare and profit maximization, which are topics in the field of computational economics (cs.EC), and the use of a secretary model suggests a focus on learning and generalization (cs.LG).
